API <p> External interface for interacting with Manthan. </p> <p></p> Purpose <p> The API receives events, executes the decision engine, and returns results.  It acts as the entry point into the system. </p> <p></p> Endpoints <pre>
GET /health
POST /internal/event
</pre> <p></p> Health Check <pre>
GET /health
</pre> <p> Returns system status. </p> <pre>
{
  "status": "ok"
}
</pre> <p></p> Event Processing <pre>
POST /internal/event
</pre> <p> Processes incoming events (e.g. GitHub PR). </p> <p></p> Input <p> Structured event payload. </p> <pre>
{
  eventPayload: { ... },
  contractId: "..."
}
</pre> <p></p> Output <pre>
{
  decision: {
    status: "pass | fail",
    failedStep: "..."
  },
  trace: { ... },
  explanation: { ... }
}
</pre> <p></p> Behavior  Receives event Loads contract Runs decision engine Generates explanation Returns result  <p></p> Determinism <p> The API does not introduce any non-determinism.  It strictly passes inputs to the engine and returns outputs. </p> <p></p> Constraints  No mutation of contract No external logic injection No randomness No hidden processing  <p></p> Summary <p> The API provides a deterministic interface to the Manthan system, ensuring that every decision request produces a consistent and traceable result. </p>

Decision Engine <p> Deterministic execution core of Manthan. </p> <p></p> Purpose <p> The decision engine evaluates inputs against contracts and produces:  a deterministic outcome with a full execution trace. </p> <p></p> Execution Pipeline <pre>
contract_validation
→ determinism_check
→ boundary_check
→ intent_alignment
→ base_rules
</pre> <p> Each step is executed in a fixed order.   Failure at any step stops execution immediately. </p> <p></p> Step Breakdown <p> contract_validation Ensures contract structure and rules are valid. determinism_check Prevents forbidden patterns and non-deterministic behavior. boundary_check Ensures execution stays within defined system boundaries. intent_alignment Validates that changes match declared intent. base_rules Applies core rule evaluation defined by the contract. </p> <p></p> Execution Properties  Fixed step order Fail-fast execution No randomness No external calls No hidden state  <p></p> Output Structure <pre>
{
  decision: {
    status: "pass | fail",
    failedStep: "..."
  },
  trace: {
    evaluationSteps: [...]
  }
}
</pre> <p></p> Determinism Guarantee <p> For the same:  Input + Contract  The engine will always produce:  the exact same output. </p> <p></p> What This Is NOT  Not AI generation Not probabilistic reasoning Not heuristic scoring Not rule guessing  <p></p> What This IS  Deterministic evaluation Contract-driven execution Fully traceable reasoning Enforced decision outcomes  <p></p> Summary <p> The decision engine ensures that every decision in Manthan is:  deterministic, explainable, and auditable by design. </p>
